                  </hi>. I am a copper-plate printer, and live in Cloth Fair, Smithfield—the prisoner was my apprentice. On the 26th of July, a little before seven o'clock, he got up, and left my house—he had no business to go—the waistcoat and boots belong to my lad, and I missed the cards—the officer brought him to me—they are mine.</p>
